---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const LGUS = [
  "Caloocan", "Las_Pinas", "Makati", "Malabon", "Mandaluyong",
  "Manila", "Marikina", "Muntinlupa", "Navotas", "Paranaque",
  "Pasay", "Pasig", "Pateros", "Quezon_City", "San_Juan",
  "Taguig", "Valenzuela",
];

const RANKED = [
  { lgu: "Quezon_City", v0: 19.53, clf: 18.74, delta: -0.79, newpp: 4.33, drop: 5.11 },
  { lgu: "Mandaluyong", v0: 10.59, clf: 12.11, delta: 1.51, newpp: 4.64, drop: 3.12 },
  { lgu: "Taguig", v0: 8.24, clf: 10.22, delta: 1.98, newpp: 4.62, drop: 2.63 },
  { lgu: "Makati", v0: 7.89, clf: 8.61, delta: 0.71, newpp: 4.54, drop: 3.82 },
  { lgu: "Valenzuela", v0: 7.64, clf: 7.56, delta: -0.09, newpp: 4.88, drop: 4.97 },
  { lgu: "Marikina", v0: 8.43, clf: 7.51, delta: -0.91, newpp: 4.59, drop: 5.50 },
  { lgu: "Caloocan", v0: 8.79, clf: 5.79, delta: -3.00, newpp: 3.02, drop: 6.02 },
  { lgu: "Malabon", v0: 5.28, clf: 5.60, delta: 0.32, newpp: 4.16, drop: 3.84 },
  { lgu: "Pasig", v0: 5.60, clf: 3.84, delta: -1.76, newpp: 2.45, drop: 4.22 },
  { lgu: "Muntinlupa", v0: 3.61, clf: 3.51, delta: -0.10, newpp: 2.06, drop: 2.15 },
  { lgu: "Las_Pinas", v0: 4.58, clf: 3.26, delta: -1.32, newpp: 2.01, drop: 3.32 },
  { lgu: "Paranaque", v0: 3.12, clf: 2.12, delta: -1.00, newpp: 1.44, drop: 2.44 },
  { lgu: "Pasay", v0: 2.50, clf: 2.10, delta: -0.40, newpp: 0.84, drop: 1.25 },
  { lgu: "Pateros", v0: 4.68, clf: 0.84, delta: -3.84, newpp: 0.80, drop: 4.64 },
  { lgu: "Manila", v0: 0.69, clf: 0.52, delta: -0.17, newpp: 0.41, drop: 0.58 },
  { lgu: "Navotas", v0: 0.39, clf: 0.45, delta: 0.06, newpp: 0.34, drop: 0.28 },
  { lgu: "San_Juan", v0: 2.31, clf: 0.21, delta: -2.10, newpp: 0.20, drop: 2.29 },
];
---
<Base title="Leaves.PH · model validation" pathname="/validation">
  <article class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-12 pb-16 text-ink-900">
    <p class="kicker mb-4 text-sepia-500">SECTION 5 · VALIDATION GALLERY · DETECTION MODEL · t=0·60</p>
    <h1 class="font-display font-medium tracking-tight text-ink-900 mb-3"
        style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.05;">
      Per-LGU visual validation of the detection model.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-[15px] text-ink-700 leading-[1.6] mb-5 max-w-[68ch]">
      One panel per city. Each lays the model's canopy reading over the satellite
      image so you can see, block by block, where it agrees with the simpler NDVI
      rule and where the two differ. The table below ranks the 17 LGUs by how much
      canopy the model reads.
    </p>

    <div class="mb-6 inline-flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 text-[13px] text-ink-700 border border-ink-900/15 rounded px-4 py-3 bg-paper-tint/40">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm" style="background:#b65724"></span>NDVI v0 baseline</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm" style="background:#3a6c4b"></span>model-confirmed canopy</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm" style="background:#b6a020"></span>model differs from NDVI <span class="text-sepia-500">(a difference, not a verified correction)</span></span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-[14px] text-ink-500 leading-[1.6] mb-8 max-w-[68ch]">
      Under the hood, the detection model is a CLIP ViT-Large/14 head with a
      gradient-boosted regression onto Meta's 1 m canopy fraction; on held-out
      locations it reaches R&sup2; 0.83 to 0.86 under grouped cross-validation
      against Meta's 1 m reference (its calibration target, not independent ground
      truth), and is in optimization toward a first release. Panels are sorted by
      the model's canopy percentage at threshold t = 0.60.
    </p>

    <table class="w-full text-[13px] mb-10 font-mono tabular-nums">
      <thead class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-sepia-500">
        <tr class="border-b border-ink-900">
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">№</th>
          <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium">LGU</th>
          <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium">NDVI v0</th>
          <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium">Model %</th>
          <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium hidden sm:table-cell">Δ pp</th>
          <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium hidden sm:table-cell">NEW pp</th>
          <th class="text-right py-2 font-medium hidden sm:table-cell">dropped pp</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-ink-300/50 font-sans">
        {RANKED.map((r, i) => (
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 text-sepia-500 font-mono">{String(i+1).padStart(2,"0")}</td>
            <td class="py-2 font-medium">{r.lgu.replace(/_/g, " ")}</td>
            <td class="py-2 text-right font-mono">{r.v0.toFixed(2)}%</td>
            <td class="py-2 text-right font-mono text-forest-700 font-medium">{r.clf.toFixed(2)}%</td>
            <td class="py-2 text-right font-mono hidden sm:table-cell" style={r.delta < 0 ? "color:#8b3f1d" : "color:#1f6634"}>
              {r.delta > 0 ? "+" : ""}{r.delta.toFixed(2)}
            </td>
            <td class="py-2 text-right font-mono hidden sm:table-cell" style="color:#b6a020">+{r.newpp.toFixed(2)}</td>
            <td class="py-2 text-right font-mono hidden sm:table-cell" style="color:#8b3f1d">−{r.drop.toFixed(2)}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <hr class="rule-ornament my-10" />

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8">
      {RANKED.map((r) => (
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`/validation/validation_${r.lgu}_t60.png`}
            alt={`Validation panel for ${r.lgu.replace(/_/g, " ")}: S-2 RGB, NDVI v0 baseline (orange), detection model shared (green), detection model NEW additions (yellow), stats panel.`}
            class="block w-full h-auto border border-ink-900"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="fig-caption mt-2 flex flex-wrap justify-between gap-2">
            <span><span class="dateline">VAL · {r.lgu.replace(/_/g, " ")}</span> · NDVI {r.v0.toFixed(2)}% / model {r.clf.toFixed(2)}% / Δ {(r.delta > 0 ? "+" : "")}{r.delta.toFixed(2)} pp</span>
            <span class="text-sepia-500">t = 0·60</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-[14px] text-sepia-500 mt-12 leading-[1.6] max-w-[68ch]">
      The scan scripts that build these panels are in the <a href="https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph/tree/main/detection/scan" class="no-underline text-umber-700">public repository</a> (the per-year probability rasters and threshold sweeps are research-track and regenerable, not committed).
      Per-LGU table + full pipeline in <a href="/methodology" class="no-underline text-umber-700">/methodology</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
